<span id="freeTextContainer4603637087707921012">This read was a heartbreaking tragedy of Palestinians <br/>Palestine the occupied state and the misery of its people<br/>as an Arab, I grew up with stories about Palestine and its long-suffering people but even I haven&apos;t imagined it to be this horrifying. as the Author note says: The characters in this book are fictitious but Palestine and the events that happened in the book are real. <br/>The story follows Amal, a Palestinian girl, born in a refugee camp. she struggles in her life as a Palestinian living und</span>
  <span id="freeText4603637087707921012" style="display:none">This read was a heartbreaking tragedy of Palestinians <br />Palestine the occupied state and the misery of its people<br />as an Arab, I grew up with stories about Palestine and its long-suffering people but even I haven't imagined it to be this horrifying. as the Author note says: The characters in this book are fictitious but Palestine and the events that happened in the book are real. <br />The story follows Amal, a Palestinian girl, born in a refugee camp. she struggles in her life as a Palestinian living under the Israeli occupation, she still manages to find happiness even but it crumbles. she has lost so much and gained so little. <br />the story during WW II in 1941 when the Jews were fleeing the Nazis and the Holocaust. friendships are born between Palestinians and Jews. Human emotions can overcome all prejudices. <br />why I rated this 4 stars instead of 5? sadly the writer failed to capture some moments correctly and write them in the sense they needed to be written in. the writing felt kind of mediocre at times. <br />I loved the quotation from Gibran and other notables poets <br /></span>
